<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 26; Nasdaq Slips 15  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed at the start of trading today
after a pair of technology companies released vastly different
profit forecasts, leading investors to question the outlook for
corporate earnings in the current quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after the start of trading, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 26.43 at 10,640.49.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index was up 4.93 at 1,461.88, and the Nasdaq composite index
was down 15.55 at 3,859.29.
</P>
<P>
   Corning Inc. released an upbeat profit outlook, sending its
shares sharply higher. But Citrix Systems Inc., a maker of computer
network products, said its earnings will miss estimates in the
coming quarter.
</P>
