   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned mostly lower Monday after a pair
of technology companies released vastly different profit forecasts,
leading investors to question the outlook for corporate earnings in
the current quarter.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading on Wall Street, the Nasdaq composite index was
down 83.92 at 3,790.92.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones industrial average was down 20.51 at 10,593.55,
and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was down 5.57 at 1,451.38. Both
indexes had given up early gains.
</P>
