<HEADLINE> Norman Rockwell House Up for Sale  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   STOCKBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) -- The home where artist Norman Rockwell
spent the last 25 years of his life is up for sale.
</P>
<P>
   But don't expect the 14-room home, built in 1783, to become the
Rockwell Bed &AMP; Breakfast or the Rockwell Antiques Shop. A
restriction in the deed prevents the use of the Rockwell name for
any commercial purpose.
</P>
<P>
   Rockwell lived in the house from 1953 until his death in 1978 at
the age of 84. His wife, Molly, lived in the house until her death
in 1985.
</P>
<P>
   The current owners, Richard Herrick and his wife, Elizabeth
Holtzinger, are asking $775,000 for the two-story Victorian home.
</P>
<P>
   Holtzinger purchased the home for $390,000 in 1986 following the
death of Rockwell's widow. Herrick said the couple wanted a smaller
home now that their children are grown.
</P>
</TEXT>
