<HEADLINE> Albright Praises Truman Building  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright praised
Missouri's congressional delegation for winning unanimous approval
of a bill to designate the headquarters of the State Department as
the Harry S Truman Federal Building.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is entirely appropriate,'' Albright said Monday, citing
the founding of the United Nations, the launching of the Marshall
Plan for the economic recovery of Germany after World War II and
other foreign policy initiative under the former president.
</P>
<P>
   ''President Truman understood well the importance of effective
diplomacy,'' Albright said.
</P>
<P>
   The bill cleared the House in May. The Senate is expected to
complete action soon.
