<HEADLINE> Bolivian Students Demand University  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LA PAZ, Bolivia (AP) -- Tens of thousands of students and parents
from neighboring El Alto marched Monday through downtown La Paz
demanding the creation of an independent university.
</P>
<P>
   The protests paralyzed most downtown traffic in La Paz. Hundreds
of police officers were mobilized throughout the city to curb any
violence.
</P>
<P>
   A similar protest last month resulted in violent confrontations
and the ransacking of the El Alto Municipal building.
</P>
<P>
   El Alto, an impoverished city of half a million, is inhabited
mainly by Aymara Indians and does not have a government-run
university. El Alto sits on a flat plateau that borders La Paz, the
seat of government.
</P>
<P>
   The government has offered to build a university in El Alto but
insists it be a branch of the San Andres University that is based
in La Paz.
</P>
</TEXT>
