<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000612.0069 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-12 16:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Corning Inc., up $19 at $231
</P>
<P>
   The company said it anticipates earnings for the second quarter
to be 78 cents to 80 cents a share, well above analysts' estimates
of 69 cents a share. Corning expects profits to come in about 50
percent above last year's second-quarter totals.
</P>
<P>
Nike Inc., down $1.125 at $40.438
</P>
<P>
   Goldman Sachs said Nike should earn 73 to 74 cents in its first
fiscal quarter, compared with analysts' estimates of 77 cents.
Analyst Margaret Mager said Nike stock is likely to tread water
until improving retail trends translate into more robust orders.
</P>
<P>
Keithley Instruments, up $7.938 at $57.875
</P>
<P>
   Investor's Business Daily included Keithley in a section titled
''The New America.'' The newspaper said that with demand for new
chips running high, demand for Keithley's test and measurement
equipment should increase.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Citrix Systems Inc., down $18.938 at $22.25
</P>
<P>
   The company, a maker of computer network products, said its
earnings will miss estimates in the coming quarter. Citrix said
expansion of its core business in large enterprise accounts is
taking place slower than expected.
</P>
<P>
Alkermes Inc., down $15.75 at $38.50
</P>
<P>
   The maker of drug delivery systems, said Johnson &AMP; Johnson has
ended development of an injectable, sustained-release version of
the anemia drug erythropoietin. Alkermes was collaborating with the
pharmaceutical giant on the new version of the drug, but Johnson &AMP;
Johnson wants to concentrate on other means of developing it.
</P>
<P>
IBasis Inc., up $7.50 at $32.875
</P>
<P>
   The company confirmed it signed a telephony contract with China
Mobile Telecommunications Corp., which claims the world's biggest
base of cell-phone users. IBasis is an Internet-based
communications company.
</P>
<P>
Caldera Systems Inc., up $2.75 at $14.50
</P>
<P>
   The company has been added to the Russell 3000 Index, which
measures the performance of the 3,000 largest U.S. companies.
Caldera makes specialized servers and Internet access devices for
the Linux operating system.
</P>
