<HEADLINE> Victims of Ocean City boat crash listed  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Following are the names, ages, hometowns and
conditions of the
victims of a fatal boat accident in Ocean City, N.J., as provided
by State Police and two hospitals.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Two people were killed Sunday when a 26-foot speedboat was
broadsided by a 30-foot cabin cruiser. One or two other occupants
of the smaller boat, who were knocked overboard, remained missing
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Of the nine people aboard the cabin cruiser, only one was
hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
   DEAD
</P>
<P>
   -Dominick Laspata, 26, of Westville, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   -John Flynn, 42, of Sicklerville, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   MISSING
</P>
<P>
   -James G. Fisler, 25, of Sewell, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   INJURED
</P>
<P>
   -James Swiggard, 18, of Norristown, Pa., suffered a head injury,
broken arm, facial lacerations and water in the lungs. He was taken
to Shore Memorial Hospital in Somers Point, N.J., and then
transferred to Atlantic City Medical Center, where he was listed in
serious condition.
</P>
<P>
   -William P. Gill, 18, of Lansdale, Pa., suffered leg bruises and
a dental injury but was treated and released from Shore Memorial
Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   -Ken Meyers, 19, of Lansdale, Pa., suffered minor head injuries
and arm injuries and was released from Shore Memorial Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   -Kara Ketterer, 18, of Lansdale, Pa., suffered facial injuries
and a neck sprain. She was treated and released from Shore Memorial
Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   OTHERS
</P>
<P>
   -John Lego, 52, of Lansdale, Pa., the driver of the cabin
cruiser, suffered minor injuries but was not taken to a hospital.
</P>
<P>
   -Alex Johnson, 17, of North Wales, Pa., was unhurt.
</P>
<P>
   -Megan Heath, 17, of Lansdale, Pa., was unhurt.
</P>
<P>
   -Pam Howley, 17, of Lansdale, Pa., was unhurt.
</P>
