<HEADLINE> State Farm to return $100 million on Florida car policies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) - Some 2.2 million Floridians who insure
their cars with State Farm will get dividends, the insurer said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The average dividend in Florida will be $45, said Tom Hagerty,
with the company's Winter Haven office.
</P>
<P>
   The total paid to Florida customers will be $100.3 million,
according to a release issue from State Farm's headquarters in
Bloomington, Ill.
</P>
<P>
   The dividends are being paid to all customers of State Farm
Mutual Automobile Insurance Co. across the country except in New
Jersey.
</P>
<P>
   Policyholders who have a dividend of more than $10 will receive
a check and those with dividends of less than $10 will get a credit
on their next premium, Hagerty said.
</P>
<P>
   Payments will be made over the next six months starting Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Dividends are a one-time return of premium paid after State Farm
enjoys better-than-expected financial results.
</P>
</TEXT>
