<HEADLINE> Man dies in bar fight; parolee arrested  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROME, N.Y. (AP) - Police arrested a 22-year-old man on parole
for burglary and accused him of physically assaulting another man
who died after a bar fight on the city's south side.
</P>
<P>
   Lawrence Chmielewski, 44, was taken to Rome Memorial Hospital
after the altercation Sunday night and pronounced dead at 9:20
p.m., police said. An autopsy was conducted Monday at St. Elizabeth
Medical Center in nearby Utica.
</P>
<P>
   Police apprehended James Vance, who was arraigned Monday on a
manslaughter charge. He requested that the public defender's office
represent him.
</P>
<P>
   Judge Daniel C. Wilson ordered Vance held without bail until it
could be determined if he had more than one felony conviction on
his record. A hearing was set for Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Police responding to a 911 call found Chmielewski on the floor
of the bar, unconscious and bleeding from his head, nose and mouth.
The two men apparently knew each other, police said.
</P>
<P>
   ''They were together playing pool and some type of dispute broke
out,'' Police Chief Merino Ciccone said.
</P>
<P>
   Officials said they were looking at whether any weapons were
used in the attack.
</P>
<P>
   In 1997, Vance and another man were charged with burglarizing
pharmacies in Boonville and Holland Patent. They were accused of
stealing thousands of dollars worth of prescription drugs and
instant lottery tickets.
</P>
<P>
   Vance was sentenced to 2{ to 7 years in state prison. He was
released in September 1998 to the state parole division.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Chmielewski had been injured before in fights
outside at least two other bars in the city in the last three
years.
</P>
</TEXT>
